3. Permitted Use

The Software may be used for the following purposes:

• personal use
• academic research
• evaluation of the Nyx runtime system
• development of programs intended to run on the Nyx VM

Users may compile and execute the Software for these purposes.

---

4. Distribution Restrictions

The Software may not be redistributed independently without explicit
written permission from the Author.

Distribution is permitted only when the Nyx VM is included as an
integral component of the official Nyx platform or runtime environment.

Redistribution of modified or standalone versions of the Nyx VM
is prohibited.

---

5. Derivative Works

You may not create or distribute derivative works based on the
Nyx VM implementation.

This includes:

• modified runtime engines
• reimplemented execution engines derived from the Software
• repackaged versions of the Nyx VM

Derivative experimentation for personal research may be permitted,
but such works may not be published or distributed.

---

6. Competing Virtual Machines

The Nyx VM may not be used to develop competing virtual machine
technologies derived directly from the Software.

This includes but is not limited to:

• bytecode virtual machines
• runtime execution engines
• language runtime systems

where the implementation is derived directly from the Nyx VM codebase.

---

7. Artificial Intelligence Use

Artificial intelligence systems may analyze the Software for purposes
including:

• research and education
• documentation generation
• developer assistance
• generating programs that run on the Nyx VM

However, artificial intelligence systems may NOT:

• reproduce substantial portions of the Nyx VM source code
• generate a clone or functional reproduction of the Nyx VM
• distribute models containing significant portions of the Software.

---

8. Commercial Use

Commercial use of the Nyx VM requires a separate written license
agreement with the Author.

Commercial use includes but is not limited to:

• embedding the Nyx VM in commercial software products
• enterprise runtime environments
• hosted runtime services
• cloud execution platforms.

